Author: DanDan
Title: [ANN][ICO]🌈🌈🌈VECTOR - MAKE MONEY WITH THIS CRYPTO EXCHANGE 🌈🌈🌈
Body: Please enlighten me some here. Your FAQs on your website are a bit of a turnoff. "Is Vector Decentralized? No." That's a lazy answer. Please explain, because I'm seeing new decentralized exchanges to be more promising. Why did you choose this approach?  I'm all for better customer support, but how are you planning to implement that? You say 24/7 phone support, but I don't see the plans on whether you are hiring that staff yourself or outsourcing it, which usually means a lower quality standard. You may have plans for support to set you apart, but that should be a given. I wouldn't lean on that for the main service as a unique feature towards your product.  Looking forward to some feedback and clarification. Thanks!

Author: nsummy
Title: [ANN][ICO]🌈🌈🌈VECTOR - MAKE MONEY WITH THIS CRYPTO EXCHANGE 🌈🌈🌈
Body: Good idea but wayyyyy too short on details.   Seems like the only "innovation" offered is good customer service and an app.  No mockups of what the interface will look like or how the usability will be better.  No plans on how you will employ the customer service reps needed, what languages offered, how you will scale, nor a budget for any of this.  No security expert on the team (arguably the most important job).    No plans on how you will navigate the regulatory minefields of dealing with fiat and customer records.  If you look at companies like Coinbase, the reason their service is so poor is due to the fact that they grew so quickly.  They were overwhelmed and could not handle support requests.  To do what you want to do will require much more planning.  I'm not saying its not possible, and perhaps you already thought of this stuff, but I think more info is needed if you guys want a large investment.  That said, I do like the idea of token holders voting on the coins.  One question though, what do you do if someone owns 51% of the tokens?  Now they essentially control what goes on the exchange.

Author: BaumT
Title: [ANN][ICO]🌈🌈🌈VECTOR - MAKE MONEY WITH THIS CRYPTO EXCHANGE 🌈🌈🌈
Body: You raise a lot of very good points. Stuff like "No plans on how you will employ the customer service reps needed" is simply a hiring process. No need to specify that for prospective ICO participants.   As for if someone holds 51% of tokens, great question. This is where the voting multiplication over time comes in, although one might hold 51% of the tokens, if the other 49 percent of holders get together, they will have more votes than the whale because of our vote multiplication POS system.

Author: BaumT
Title: [ANN][ICO]🌈🌈🌈VECTOR - MAKE MONEY WITH THIS CRYPTO EXCHANGE 🌈🌈🌈
Body: Your confidence in us is exactly what we are looking for in this community

Author: BaumT
Title: [ANN][ICO]🌈🌈🌈VECTOR - MAKE MONEY WITH THIS CRYPTO EXCHANGE 🌈🌈🌈
Body: Thank you for asking  The purpose of the VCTR token is to allow users to vote on the platform. They can vote for system changes such as chanting systems, chat boxes, social functions, and MOST IMPORTANTLY which new coins will be added onto the exchange.  You see, right now exchanges just add a coin out of the blue, usually it is profit driven and there is no community say behind it, and if there is a "vote", coin shills just buy bots to inflate the vote for their own coin, making it useless.  This VCTR coin will give the community power to make the exchange in the way THEY see fit.

Author: BaumT
Title: [ANN][ICO]🌈🌈🌈VECTOR - MAKE MONEY WITH THIS CRYPTO EXCHANGE 🌈🌈🌈
Body: Are we decentralized? No.  Contract driven? No.  You posed 2 very good questions which I will answer here:  1) The voting for new coins works simply. Every single new crypto coin will want to be added onto our exchange, that is a given because it will cause their coin price to rise as it does with any other exchange. Lets just say 100 coins want to be added to our exchange, we will put these coins up for a vote (first ensuring their code has no bugs of course) and then YOU the community, will use your VCTR coins to vote for which new coin/s will be added onto our exchange. Why do we need a coin to do this, you might ask. Well as I am sure you have seen, some exchanges have tried to do voting for new coins before using twitter or reddit or google voting to gauge what the community wants. However, these attempts are always flawed and ruined with coin shills from reddit or whales who buy "bots" to influence THEIR coin getting onto the exchange. With the VCTR coin, there will be none of that. The sole people who use the Vector exchange will be the ones deciding which coins are added.  2) The coin contract creator has no right to override any decision Vector makes. If they are waiting to list their coin on exchanges for some "news" then their coin simply will not be up for vote. On the flip side, they cannot "override" Vector to get their coin onto our exchange without going through the community voting FIRST.  I hope I answered your questions sufficiently.
